<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
Externally, the species hardly differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. mishmiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="mishmiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. mishmiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schillhammer, 2004 from India, but may be distinguished by the shape of the aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 41–46" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 41 - 46. Hesperosoma motuoense sp. nov. 41 - 42 habitus 43 - 45 aedeagus, lateral (43) and ventral (44) views, paramere (45) 46 female abdominal tergite X. Scale bars: 2 mm (41 - 42), 0.2 mm (43 - 46)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.75799.figures41-46" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620012" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">43-45</figureCitation>
): median lobe (lateral view) in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. motuoense" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="motuoense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. motuoense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. broader than in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. mishmiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="mishmiense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. mishmiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, paramere in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. motuoense" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="motuoense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. motuoense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. with shallower medio-apical emargination.
</paragraph>
